WEBVTT

00:08.842 --> 00:12.136
NARRATOR: One time a year
there's a marvelous night,

00:12.220 --> 00:16.265
when enchantment and wonder
spark and take flight.

00:18.143 --> 00:22.354
Each home fills with joy
on this grand holiday,

00:22.439 --> 00:26.150
with hearts growing warm
in a magical way.

00:27.444 --> 00:30.237
The rooms are all covered
with garlands and wreaths.

00:30.280 --> 00:33.782
The mantel is ready,
with stockings beneath.

00:35.785 --> 00:39.705
Lights twinkle and glow
and bells brightly chime.

00:39.831 --> 00:44.334
The moment's arrived! It's here!
Christmas time.

01:01.436 --> 01:05.355
Three precious gifts lie under this tree.

01:05.482 --> 01:09.109
What secrets they hold?
Let's look, and we'll see.

01:11.362 --> 01:14.531
The first tells a story for us all to hear,

01:14.616 --> 01:18.911
about laughter and family
and those we hold dear.

01:21.247 --> 01:25.000
We love Christmas so much
we want it to stay,

01:25.085 --> 01:29.171
but what if we wished
it was here every day?

01:29.214 --> 01:31.173
(TICKING)

01:34.302 --> 01:35.803
(SNORING)

01:35.845 --> 01:37.721
Anchors aweigh!

01:39.516 --> 01:42.267
Full steam ahead!

01:44.020 --> 01:46.146
Swab the decks, you...

01:46.856 --> 01:49.316
(SNORING IN TUNE)

02:06.960 --> 02:08.001
(IMITATING TRAIN WHISTLE)

02:08.044 --> 02:10.586
(LAUGHING)
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

02:10.672 --> 02:11.839
(BOTH LAUGHING)

02:15.260 --> 02:16.718
-It's here!
-The one!

02:16.803 --> 02:17.803
The only!

02:17.887 --> 02:19.930
ALL: Best day of the year!

02:20.014 --> 02:21.557
It's Christmas!

02:30.775 --> 02:33.819
Oh, boy! Just what we always wanted!

02:33.903 --> 02:35.154
Hey, look at this!

02:35.363 --> 02:36.363
Cool!

02:36.447 --> 02:39.575
Merry Christmas, boys! What the...
(EXCLAIMS)

02:44.289 --> 02:45.747
(CLATTERING)

02:48.626 --> 02:52.421
You know we have to wait for the family!

02:52.881 --> 02:54.715
Sorry, Uncle Donald.

03:00.221 --> 03:02.931
Aw... It's Christmas,

03:03.057 --> 03:06.393
and I've got a special surprise for you!

03:10.607 --> 03:12.399
ALL: Yeah! (LAUGHING)

03:16.654 --> 03:18.488
But, boys, you didn't... (GRUNTS)

03:18.615 --> 03:19.615
HUEY: Sorry, Uncle Donald.

03:19.657 --> 03:21.158
-...even read the...
-DEWEY: Sorry, Uncle Donald.

03:21.242 --> 03:23.202
-...card!
-Bye, Uncle Donald.

03:23.453 --> 03:24.620
-We'll read it later.
-(SIGHS)

03:26.122 --> 03:27.664
Merry Christmas, everybody!

03:27.749 --> 03:29.458
Merry Christmas, indeed!

03:29.542 --> 03:32.586
Where are my boys?
Where are my kisses?

03:32.712 --> 03:34.963
Oh, I could just eat you up!
(CHUCKLES)

03:36.007 --> 03:37.966
-(KISSING)
-(BOYS GRUNTING)

03:39.052 --> 03:41.803
Oh... Ugh! Ew...

03:44.515 --> 03:46.808
DAISY: Oh, Donald?

03:50.813 --> 03:52.147
(GULPS)

03:52.273 --> 03:54.399
Oh, boy, oh, boy, oh, boy!

03:55.777 --> 03:58.820
HUEY: Hi, Daisy! Bye, Daisy.
Catch you later!

04:01.074 --> 04:02.658
(ALL LAUGHING)

04:02.700 --> 04:04.284
Yow!

04:05.703 --> 04:07.079
(GOBBLING)

04:07.622 --> 04:09.873
LOUIE: Last one down the hill's
a rotten egg!

04:09.958 --> 04:11.124
DEWEY: Not me!

04:14.671 --> 04:16.838
Boys? Dinner!

04:18.007 --> 04:19.341
If there's one thing better...

04:19.425 --> 04:20.801
...than Christmas presents...

04:20.843 --> 04:22.386
...it's Christmas dinner!

04:22.595 --> 04:24.596
Isn't this lovely?

04:24.722 --> 04:27.307
All of us gathered for a wonderful meal?

04:27.433 --> 04:30.519
I think this is
my favorite part of Christmas.

04:32.355 --> 04:34.523
Ooh! Turkey!

04:34.816 --> 04:37.526
Donald? Would you like to carve?

04:37.860 --> 04:38.860
(GOBBLING)

04:40.697 --> 04:43.657
Boys! Where are your manners?

04:44.951 --> 04:46.118
(BURPS)

04:48.204 --> 04:49.997
This turkey is so good!

04:50.039 --> 04:51.748
Your gravy never has lumps!

04:52.041 --> 04:54.710
ALL: We love your cooking, Aunt Daisy!

04:54.752 --> 04:56.003
(YELLING)

04:57.422 --> 05:00.841
Donald! They're just enjoying
my Christmas dinner.

05:01.801 --> 05:03.802
Ah, phooey! (MUTTERS)

05:05.054 --> 05:07.097
All right. Who's for caroling?

05:07.724 --> 05:09.808
Aw, we don't want to sing,
Uncle Scrooge!

05:09.892 --> 05:11.935
We want to play with our toys!

05:12.061 --> 05:14.146
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

05:14.230 --> 05:18.066
We wish you a merry Christmas

05:18.151 --> 05:20.110
And a happy New Year

05:20.403 --> 05:21.737
(CHIMING)

05:22.697 --> 05:24.698
DONALD: Bedtime, boys.

05:24.782 --> 05:28.493
Not yet!
Christmas can't be over already.

05:28.619 --> 05:30.370
Good night, boys!

05:33.374 --> 05:34.374
Aw!

05:37.086 --> 05:40.255
-What a great day!
-We should do it more often.

05:40.923 --> 05:43.258
Yeah! Once a week should be enough.

05:45.887 --> 05:51.183
It'll be another 365 days
until we get more Christmas.

05:51.768 --> 05:53.769
"Star light, star bright,

05:54.354 --> 05:56.438
"First star I see tonight,

05:56.522 --> 05:59.441
"I wish I may, I wish I might

05:59.859 --> 06:01.943
"Have the wish I wish tonight."

06:01.986 --> 06:05.447
ALL: We wish
it was Christmas every day.

06:17.126 --> 06:18.460
(IMITATING TRAIN WHISTLE)

06:18.503 --> 06:20.921
(LAUGHING)
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

06:20.963 --> 06:22.214
(BOTH LAUGHING)

06:22.298 --> 06:23.965
(SNORING)

06:26.636 --> 06:29.971
Boy, those guys sure
like that choo-choo.

06:30.181 --> 06:32.432
They gotta play with
that thing again today?

06:32.475 --> 06:34.893
Hey! Let's play with our new toys.

06:35.853 --> 06:36.853
LOUIE: Whoa!

06:37.855 --> 06:39.314
They're gone.

06:43.069 --> 06:45.737
Hey! What is this?

06:51.911 --> 06:54.371
DEWEY: (GASPS) Whoa!

06:55.415 --> 06:57.833
Didn't we open these yesterday?

06:58.292 --> 07:01.128
Are you thinking what I'm thinking?

07:01.421 --> 07:03.880
There's only one way to find out.

07:04.006 --> 07:07.467
We're gonna have to open
these presents.

07:09.846 --> 07:11.138
(RATTLING)

07:12.932 --> 07:15.016
DONALD: Merry Christmas!

07:15.059 --> 07:17.811
(ALL SCREAMING)

07:19.021 --> 07:20.439
(SCREAMING)

07:25.736 --> 07:28.113
-Whoa!
-Uncle Donald, we did it.

07:28.197 --> 07:30.449
It's Christmas again. Uncle Donald...

07:30.533 --> 07:32.993
It's Christmas again, Uncle Donald.

07:33.035 --> 07:34.453
TWo days in a row!

07:35.997 --> 07:37.372
Aw!

07:37.915 --> 07:40.125
You boys must have been dreaming.

07:41.294 --> 07:44.629
Hey! We almost forgot
about our special surprise!

07:48.676 --> 07:49.676
Whoa!

07:49.844 --> 07:51.303
Where are my kisses?

07:51.387 --> 07:53.680
Oh, I could just eat you up!
(CHUCKLES)

07:53.848 --> 07:55.765
-(KISSING)
-(BOYS GRUNTING)

07:56.684 --> 07:58.059
Oh...

07:59.187 --> 08:00.395
(SPITTING)

08:00.438 --> 08:02.647
We should have seen that one coming.

08:03.816 --> 08:05.442
(BOYS LAUGHING)

08:08.029 --> 08:11.072
Last one down the hill's a rotten egg!

08:11.949 --> 08:12.991
Again!

08:13.075 --> 08:14.117
(GOBBLING)

08:14.785 --> 08:17.078
Boys? Dinner!

08:19.373 --> 08:21.416
Isn't this lovely?

08:21.584 --> 08:24.085
All of us gathered for a wonderful meal?

08:24.253 --> 08:27.380
I think this is
my favorite part of Christmas.

08:28.007 --> 08:30.050
Ooh, turkey!

08:30.176 --> 08:34.179
Boys! Where are your manners?

08:35.014 --> 08:37.599
(BURPING)

08:37.892 --> 08:39.058
(YELLING)

08:39.101 --> 08:42.562
Donald! They're just enjoying
my Christmas dinner.

08:44.315 --> 08:45.315
(GULPS)

08:46.234 --> 08:48.151
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

08:48.236 --> 08:50.028
We wish you a merry Christmas

08:50.112 --> 08:51.279
(CHIMING)

08:51.322 --> 08:52.614
Good night, boys!

08:55.660 --> 08:56.660
(LAUGHING)

08:56.744 --> 08:58.119
That was great!

08:58.204 --> 08:59.371
Double great!

08:59.455 --> 09:01.456
Ah! Yeah.

09:06.754 --> 09:07.879
(IMITATING TRAIN WHISTLE)

09:07.964 --> 09:10.048
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

09:10.299 --> 09:11.341
(BOTH LAUGHING)

09:12.176 --> 09:14.052
-Yeah!
-All right!

09:14.971 --> 09:17.055
Merry Christmas, boys.

09:17.181 --> 09:18.682
Huh? (EXCLAIMS)

09:19.141 --> 09:21.184
-Look out, Uncle Donald.
-(CLATTERING)

09:25.356 --> 09:27.065
Merry Christmas, everybody!

09:27.149 --> 09:28.775
Merry Christmas, indeed!

09:28.818 --> 09:31.945
Where are my boys?
Where are my kisses?

09:31.988 --> 09:33.154
(ALL YELLING)

09:34.532 --> 09:36.408
DONALD: Oh, no, you don't.
I'm gonna make you...

09:36.492 --> 09:37.701
(BOYS PROTESTING)

09:37.827 --> 09:39.995
-AUNT GERTIE: Oh! (KISSING)
-(BOYS GRUNTING)

09:41.289 --> 09:42.497
(ALL LAUGHING)

09:45.668 --> 09:49.045
DAISY: I think this is
my favorite part of Christmas.

09:49.130 --> 09:50.338
(BURPS)

09:51.465 --> 09:53.174
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

09:53.259 --> 09:55.176
-(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)
-(CHIPMUNKS LAUGHING)

09:55.261 --> 09:57.679
Merry Christmas, boys!

09:57.763 --> 09:59.681
Huh? (EXCLAIMS)

09:59.724 --> 10:01.474
(CLANGING)

10:01.517 --> 10:02.601
(DOOR OPENS)

10:02.685 --> 10:04.060
DAISY: Merry Christmas, everybody!

10:04.145 --> 10:05.478
Oh, I could just eat you up!

10:05.646 --> 10:08.607
DAISY: This is
my favorite part of Christmas.

10:10.234 --> 10:12.110
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

10:12.194 --> 10:13.194
(CHIMING)

10:13.279 --> 10:14.279
(DALE IMITATING TRAIN WHISTLE)

10:14.363 --> 10:15.697
CHIP: (LAUGHING) All aboard.
Next stop, Waterville!

10:15.740 --> 10:16.781
(BOTH LAUGHING)

10:16.866 --> 10:18.908
You can stop Christmas now!

10:18.993 --> 10:20.368
-Please!
-Please!

10:21.495 --> 10:22.704
(CHIMING)

10:23.080 --> 10:24.706
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

10:24.749 --> 10:25.749
Where are my kisses?

10:25.833 --> 10:27.000
(CHIMING)

10:27.043 --> 10:28.960
(LAUGHING)
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

10:29.045 --> 10:31.171
-...favorite part of Christmas.
-(CHIMING)

10:31.213 --> 10:32.297
Who's for caroling?

10:32.381 --> 10:34.215
-(CHIMING)
-(YELLING)

10:34.383 --> 10:36.343
(LAUGHING)
All aboard. Next stop, Waterville!

10:38.387 --> 10:39.512
(DALE IMITATING
TRAIN WHISTLING)

10:40.306 --> 10:41.514
(BOTH YELLING)

10:43.893 --> 10:46.019
(CHUCKLES) Looks like
the end of the line!

10:46.062 --> 10:47.103
(CHIPMUNKS LAUGHING)

10:47.188 --> 10:48.730
Until tomorrow.

10:48.773 --> 10:51.232
When it happens all over again.

10:51.692 --> 10:54.736
You're right. Yesterday's today,

10:54.820 --> 10:58.907
and today is tomorrow,
and it's gonna be the same thing,

10:59.075 --> 11:01.701
day in and day out,
and day in and day out...

11:01.744 --> 11:03.995
Hey! What's wrong? Get a grip!

11:05.915 --> 11:07.582
I'm sorry, fellas.

11:09.251 --> 11:11.378
That's okay. We know how you feel.

11:11.420 --> 11:14.631
If I see the same toys again,
I'll go out of my mind!

11:14.882 --> 11:17.342
Yeah, and if I eat any more turkey,

11:17.426 --> 11:19.928
(CHUCKLES)
I'm gonna need new clothes!

11:20.221 --> 11:23.848
We gotta do something
to liven things up.

11:28.396 --> 11:30.188
LOUIE: (IMITATES STATIC)
Green Leader to Red Leader.

11:32.608 --> 11:35.944
DEWEY: (IMITATES STATIC)
Initiate Pancake Intercept Sequence.

11:36.529 --> 11:37.612
LOUIE: (IMITATES STATIC) Roger.

11:42.159 --> 11:43.368
(DONALD YELLING)

11:50.584 --> 11:51.584
Uh-oh.

11:52.128 --> 11:53.128
(YELLING)

11:53.212 --> 11:56.297
Donald!
Stop playing with the boys' presents.

12:03.055 --> 12:06.099
Where are my boys?
Where are my kisses?

12:06.142 --> 12:07.142
Ooh!

12:07.268 --> 12:08.309
Oh...

12:08.352 --> 12:10.353
Right here, Aunt Gertie.

12:14.442 --> 12:16.067
(BOYS LAUGHING)

12:19.447 --> 12:21.406
Isn't this lovely?

12:21.574 --> 12:24.200
All of us gathered for a wonderful meal?

12:24.368 --> 12:27.328
I think this is
my favorite part of Christmas.

12:28.664 --> 12:30.165
-(GOBBLING)
-Oh!

12:30.249 --> 12:31.374
Turkey!

12:31.917 --> 12:32.917
(BOYS LAUGHING)

12:39.508 --> 12:40.675
(YELLING)

12:43.220 --> 12:44.763
(NOTES PLAYING)

12:47.516 --> 12:49.017
-(STRINGS POPPING)
-(THUDS)

12:50.060 --> 12:53.146
Not the piano! Not my beloved carols!

12:55.065 --> 12:56.566
-(GOBBLING)
-(YELLING)

13:01.530 --> 13:02.655
(STRUGGLING)

13:02.698 --> 13:04.199
(TURKEY YELLING)

13:05.868 --> 13:07.368
Gobble, gobble, gobble.

13:30.142 --> 13:33.186
Well, we still have the tree.

13:34.230 --> 13:35.230
(GASPS)

13:36.440 --> 13:39.400
Let's get out of here
before Uncle Donald gets mad!

13:39.568 --> 13:42.237
Hey, we'll be outside if you need us.
(GASPS)

13:56.836 --> 13:59.128
Donald? Are you all right?

14:03.384 --> 14:05.260
"To Huey, Dewey, and Louie.

14:05.845 --> 14:09.430
"Christmas isn't about
candy canes, holly,

14:09.557 --> 14:11.474
"or lights all aglow.

14:11.600 --> 14:17.313
"It's about the hearts that we touch
and the care that we show.

14:18.274 --> 14:20.608
"Wishing you lots of love,

14:20.943 --> 14:22.944
"Donald and Daisy."

14:25.531 --> 14:28.199
Oh, some Christmas
this turned out to be.

14:37.001 --> 14:42.255
Gee, I don't know about you guys,
but I don't ever want to do that again.

14:42.923 --> 14:45.466
-Me too.
-Me three.

14:46.385 --> 14:50.597
DEWEY: Tomorrow, let's have
the best Christmas ever.

14:54.852 --> 14:56.144
(GRUNTING)

14:56.186 --> 14:58.730
We're sure putting
these sleds to good use!

14:58.939 --> 14:59.981
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWING)

15:00.024 --> 15:01.858
DEWEY: Incoming!

15:06.071 --> 15:07.989
Merry Christmas, fellas.

15:08.657 --> 15:09.824
Huh?

15:09.950 --> 15:12.535
Look!
We made you breakfast, Uncle Donald.

15:13.120 --> 15:15.830
Aw! Isn't that nice?

15:16.957 --> 15:20.001
Hey, you want to open presents?

15:20.252 --> 15:24.422
No way, Uncle Donald.
We gotta wait for the family to get here.

15:27.009 --> 15:28.843
Merry Christmas, everybody!

15:28.886 --> 15:30.845
Merry Christmas, indeed!

15:30.888 --> 15:33.640
Don't forget our Christmas kisses,
Aunt Gertie.

15:37.561 --> 15:40.605
Hey, what are they up to?

15:40.898 --> 15:43.942
You boys are so wonderful!

15:46.987 --> 15:48.279
That looks heavy!

15:48.364 --> 15:49.697
ALL: Let us help you!

15:49.823 --> 15:52.867
Why, isn't that sweet? Thank you, boys.

15:55.037 --> 15:57.288
Ooh! Ham!

15:58.082 --> 16:00.541
Uncle Donald, would you like to carve?

16:01.210 --> 16:03.586
Something's up for sure.

16:04.171 --> 16:06.589
Nothing better than
all of us gathering together...

16:06.674 --> 16:09.926
-...for a wonderful meal.
-It's our most favorite part.

16:10.010 --> 16:11.302
(GOBBLING)

16:11.887 --> 16:13.721
My feelings exactly.

16:14.264 --> 16:16.140
How about some carols,
Uncle Scrooge?

16:16.558 --> 16:19.978
Why, boys, it's like
you could read my mind.

16:25.651 --> 16:27.568
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

16:27.611 --> 16:29.570
We wish you a merry Christmas

16:29.655 --> 16:30.905
We wish you a...

16:30.948 --> 16:33.658
What's the big idea?
What are you boys up to?

16:33.742 --> 16:37.662
Why, Donald Duck!
You're spoiling a perfect Christmas.

16:37.746 --> 16:39.872
Nah, Uncle Donald is right.

16:40.207 --> 16:41.582
We are up to something.

16:44.920 --> 16:46.838
ALL: Merry Christmas, Uncle Donald!

16:47.881 --> 16:50.675
HUEY: See?
It's your dream boat, Uncle Donald.

16:52.094 --> 16:55.263
-Oh, thank you, boys.
-(ALL LAUGHlNG)

16:58.350 --> 17:00.810
Oh, how beautiful.

17:00.894 --> 17:03.563
Some Christmas
this has turned out to be.

17:03.605 --> 17:05.815
Oh, I'm just so happy!
(LAUGHING)

17:29.673 --> 17:31.632
(SINGING) We wish you
a merry Christmas

17:31.675 --> 17:35.636
We wish you a merry Christmas

17:35.679 --> 17:41.434
And a happy New Year

17:43.187 --> 17:44.771
(ALL SNORING)

17:45.439 --> 17:47.273
DONALD: Oh, boys!

17:50.319 --> 17:51.903
Come give me a push!

17:51.987 --> 17:53.613
-(CHUCKLES)
-(DOOR OPENS)

17:55.741 --> 17:56.949
(LAUGHING)

17:58.702 --> 18:02.330
-It's over! Christmas is finally over!
-(CHEERING)

18:04.083 --> 18:06.793
The day after Christmas!

18:06.919 --> 18:10.338
Aw, I understand, boys.

18:10.506 --> 18:13.716
You wish it could be Christmas
every day.

18:13.801 --> 18:15.510
ALL: No!

18:15.844 --> 18:18.137
Anchors aweigh!

18:20.182 --> 18:22.433
Full steam ahead?

18:22.518 --> 18:24.477
Whoa! Whoa!

18:25.854 --> 18:26.979
Uh-oh!

18:27.022 --> 18:28.106
Oh, no!

18:28.190 --> 18:30.399
Man overboard!

18:30.484 --> 18:31.526
(YELLING)

18:31.568 --> 18:33.361
(GRUNTS) (SHIVERS)

18:34.571 --> 18:35.571
Whoa!

18:37.699 --> 18:40.868
DONALD: Why does this always
happen to me? I don't understand.

18:41.036 --> 18:44.372
NARRATOR: So, Christmas was meant
to last just one day,

18:44.998 --> 18:47.416
and maybe it's simply better that way.

18:47.501 --> 18:51.420
It's a time to be treasured.
It can't always be here,

18:51.505 --> 18:55.508
but the feeling it gives us
can last the whole year.

18:56.927 --> 19:01.055
Now, this gift holds a story
both wondrous and rare,

19:01.140 --> 19:04.976
about a father and a son
and the love that they share.

19:07.437 --> 19:10.356
This Christmas, they'll learn
before the night's through,

19:10.482 --> 19:14.735
if we care for each other,
our dreams can come true.

19:14.945 --> 19:18.823
GOOFY: (SINGING)
Hark, the hairy angels sing

19:18.907 --> 19:22.034
Come on, Maxie!
At least hum a few bars.

19:22.077 --> 19:23.953
MAX: Dad, hurry up!

19:24.037 --> 19:27.582
Deck the walls with cows and collies

19:27.624 --> 19:29.584
Fa la-la la la la-la la la

19:29.668 --> 19:32.295
The mailman comes at noon, Dad!

19:32.379 --> 19:34.422
Hmm, let's see now.

19:35.465 --> 19:39.051
Uh... Oh! How about one of them
snazzy electrical recliners?

19:39.094 --> 19:40.928
Yeah, Dad. Whatever.

19:41.972 --> 19:45.099
Naw, don't want to turn
into some highfalutin fancy-pants.

19:45.225 --> 19:49.937
Yeah, yeah. Great, Dad. But Santa
won't get our letter if we don't leave

19:51.148 --> 19:52.231
now!

20:00.115 --> 20:01.115
-(GASPS)
-Whoa!

20:02.951 --> 20:03.951
(YELLING)

20:04.036 --> 20:05.036
(CAR HONKING)

20:08.749 --> 20:11.626
Hold on, Dad! We're taking a shortcut.

20:13.962 --> 20:18.174
Maybe we ought to slow her down
before we break the sound barrier!

20:18.258 --> 20:21.427
-What?
-We're headed straight for the mall!

20:21.929 --> 20:23.012
Great idea!

20:23.096 --> 20:24.138
Whoa!

20:24.223 --> 20:25.556
(ALL CLAMORING)

20:28.560 --> 20:31.229
-Low bridge!
-Really? Where? Ow!

20:35.734 --> 20:38.653
Go on ahead
and stop the mailman, son!

20:38.779 --> 20:43.491
I'll be right behind you! Don't worry!
I won't let you down!

20:44.243 --> 20:45.284
(WHOOPING)

20:46.828 --> 20:48.663
-(THUDS)
-(WOMEN SCREAMING)

20:52.709 --> 20:53.834
'Scuse me!

20:59.341 --> 21:01.217
-(WOMAN SCREAMS)
-Oops!

21:01.510 --> 21:02.551
Pardon me, ma'am!

21:02.678 --> 21:04.262
Didn't mean to get fresh!

21:05.555 --> 21:07.348
(CHUCKLES)

21:15.899 --> 21:16.899
Wait! Wait!

21:28.412 --> 21:30.997
Hey! There's a madman
on the ornament!

21:31.039 --> 21:32.331
WOMAN: There he goes!

21:32.624 --> 21:34.166
MAN: What is he doing?

21:36.962 --> 21:38.170
Oh!

21:38.213 --> 21:39.255
(GASPING)

21:39.339 --> 21:40.589
(CHEERING)

21:43.677 --> 21:44.802
(SCREAMING)

21:49.057 --> 21:51.183
Oops. Sorry.

21:51.226 --> 21:53.311
(ALL SCREAMING)

21:56.440 --> 21:57.940
Wait! Stop!

21:58.317 --> 22:00.484
You have to mail our letter to Santa!

22:01.361 --> 22:03.362
Hey, get out of the road, kid!

22:03.864 --> 22:06.073
(CHILDREN LAUGHING)

22:10.579 --> 22:11.579
(CHUCKLES)

22:12.914 --> 22:14.373
(GASPS) Ow!

22:22.966 --> 22:24.717
Whoa! Wow!

22:26.720 --> 22:28.220
(YELLING)

22:29.473 --> 22:35.686
Whoa!

22:39.274 --> 22:43.611
Do you have anything bigger?
I have an empty space right here.

22:43.653 --> 22:44.653
(GASPS)

22:46.073 --> 22:47.990
Ooo! I'll take it!

22:48.367 --> 22:49.367
Phew.

22:50.452 --> 22:51.619
(YELLS)

22:53.121 --> 22:54.914
(SCREAMING)

22:59.461 --> 23:02.463
But my dad's gonna be here
any minute! Honest!

23:02.798 --> 23:04.048
Sorry, kid.

23:04.633 --> 23:05.966
-(GOOFY YELLING)
-Gotta go.

23:07.427 --> 23:09.053
(PANTING)

23:09.137 --> 23:10.304
(SLOBBERING)

23:10.555 --> 23:14.767
Special delivery for the North Pole.
(CHUCKLES)

23:15.435 --> 23:18.396
Oh, man.

23:22.526 --> 23:24.985
You really think Santa
will get the letter in time?

23:25.153 --> 23:26.737
Sure as I'm standing here.

23:26.822 --> 23:28.322
Whoa! Ow.

23:28.907 --> 23:29.949
Slippery.

23:29.991 --> 23:32.952
I gotta get it. I just gotta.

23:33.120 --> 23:37.665
My very own, one-of-a-kind,
carbon-fiber, torque-rod, snappy-flex,

23:37.707 --> 23:42.336
tip-to-tail, rail-to-rail, wooden core,
twin-directional snowboard!

23:43.755 --> 23:45.548
Phew, that's a mouthful.

23:45.632 --> 23:48.592
With adjustable forward-lean,
high-backed, skid plate,

23:48.677 --> 23:51.387
scooper-toe, step-in bindings!

23:52.180 --> 23:56.100
Look at this. All nice
and neat and ready for ol' Santy.

23:56.476 --> 23:57.935
(MACHINE HUMMING)

24:02.691 --> 24:04.275
(GRUNTING)

24:09.823 --> 24:11.866
Merry Christmas Eve, Pete!

24:12.117 --> 24:15.619
Why, if it ain't the Goofmaster himself.

24:16.204 --> 24:19.540
Say, we got us
some more work to do, Max,

24:19.666 --> 24:21.876
or Santy's never gonna
find our chimney...

24:21.918 --> 24:23.502
(YELLING)

24:23.587 --> 24:24.587
(THUDS)

24:27.382 --> 24:28.757
(LAUGHING) Ain't that quaint.

24:28.842 --> 24:31.886
The Goofbrain
thinks there's a Santy Claus.

24:32.554 --> 24:33.679
There isn't?

24:34.097 --> 24:36.015
(LAUGHING)

24:36.057 --> 24:38.184
Like father, like Goof.

24:38.226 --> 24:41.479
Kid's got the Goof gene
coursing through his bloodstream.

24:41.938 --> 24:44.064
There is too a Santa! Whoa!

24:44.733 --> 24:45.733
(GRUNTS)

24:45.817 --> 24:47.776
Aw, now, son. Come here.

24:47.861 --> 24:50.237
See, it's an urbane myth,

24:50.280 --> 24:53.407
like that, "Locked Mess Monstrosity."

24:53.700 --> 24:56.619
And the fella that brings
the sweepstakes checks, see?

24:57.037 --> 25:00.873
Well, think of it. An old guy in a red suit,

25:00.916 --> 25:04.168
cruising the whole,
entire world in one night.

25:04.252 --> 25:06.128
Using reindeer what fly?

25:06.254 --> 25:08.422
Why, it's practically impossible!

25:08.632 --> 25:11.759
Look, kid. I've been around, see?

25:11.843 --> 25:15.095
Been to all the foreign lands,
Brooklyn included.

25:15.138 --> 25:18.933
And I never seen,
nor met a soul who's seen,

25:19.059 --> 25:21.101
this Santy Claus fella.

25:22.646 --> 25:25.064
Look, Maxie! I found the front door!

25:26.191 --> 25:27.691
So long, neighbors.

25:28.193 --> 25:31.278
Have a very merry Christmas.

25:31.321 --> 25:33.072
(LAUGHING)

25:33.114 --> 25:35.115
Oh, and a happy New Year.

25:40.288 --> 25:43.165
(SINGING) Doh, doh, doh, doh,
cows and collies

25:43.291 --> 25:45.960
Di, di, di, di, di, doo, doo

25:46.086 --> 25:48.712
Hey!
How about giving your old man a hand?

25:50.215 --> 25:51.715
What is it, Maxie?

25:51.800 --> 25:55.928
Why, you look like Santy Claus
put a lump of coal in your stocking.

25:56.263 --> 25:58.722
I heard there isn't any Santa Claus.

25:58.807 --> 26:02.393
Oh, who went and told you
a silly thing like that?

26:02.477 --> 26:05.521
-Mr. Pete.
-Oh, that figures.

26:06.189 --> 26:08.482
Son, of course there's a Santy!

26:08.608 --> 26:11.735
Otherwise we'd have a lot of
out-of-work elves running around.

26:11.945 --> 26:13.028
You think?

26:13.238 --> 26:15.197
Think? Heck, I'm sure.

26:15.657 --> 26:18.617
You take it from me, son.
Have I ever been wrong?

26:19.077 --> 26:21.161
-Well...
-Why, even a broken clock

26:21.329 --> 26:23.289
is right two or three times a day.

26:23.415 --> 26:25.457
And this time, I'm right!

26:25.834 --> 26:28.794
Believe me. Santa won't let you down.

26:29.879 --> 26:31.338
Do you really think he'll come?

26:31.548 --> 26:33.674
Why, as sure as pigs fly!

26:35.677 --> 26:38.137
Hey, Dad.
What'd you ask for from Santa?

26:39.306 --> 26:41.890
Oh, you know, just the usual.

26:42.392 --> 26:43.684
What's that?

26:43.768 --> 26:45.561
(WHISPERING) It's a surprise.

26:46.104 --> 26:50.357
Now, plug her in
and let the joy of Christmas shine!

26:53.445 --> 26:54.695
(BULBS SHATTERING)

26:58.950 --> 27:01.535
-(ELECTRICITY CRACKLING)
-Wow!

27:02.370 --> 27:05.539
Phew. Now that'll put
the spirit of Christmas in you.

27:05.624 --> 27:07.833
(BOTH LAUGHING)

27:11.338 --> 27:13.130
'Course there's a Santa.

27:16.968 --> 27:19.887
GOOFY: Believe me,
Santa won't let you down.

27:21.056 --> 27:23.891
An old guy, in a red suit,

27:24.059 --> 27:27.061
cruising the whole,
entire world in one night?

27:27.187 --> 27:29.063
Using reindeer what fly?

27:29.230 --> 27:31.190
Why, it's practically impossible!

27:31.399 --> 27:33.567
Impossible! Impossible!

27:45.205 --> 27:47.414
Hiya, Maxie! Wanna help?

27:47.749 --> 27:52.086
Did you know that there were over
two billion children in the world?

27:52.212 --> 27:55.673
Hmm, no wonder
I keep tripping over roller skates.

27:55.924 --> 28:00.719
That means Santa would have to
make like 800 visits a second,

28:00.762 --> 28:02.805
not including bathroom breaks.

28:03.098 --> 28:06.100
Well, I guess ol' Santy's
been at it so long,

28:06.267 --> 28:08.435
he figured out all the shortcuts.

28:08.812 --> 28:10.270
(STRUGGLING)

28:10.939 --> 28:11.939
Oh!

28:15.235 --> 28:18.987
(CHUCKLES) Looks like it's gonna be
a white Christmas after all!

28:19.447 --> 28:21.532
Dad! This is serious!

28:21.741 --> 28:23.951
Oh, I know, son, but...

28:24.035 --> 28:25.077
(SNIFFING)

28:25.120 --> 28:28.622
Gosh, something sure smells
mighty tasty!

28:30.083 --> 28:31.083
(YELLING)

28:34.295 --> 28:35.337
Ah...

28:35.422 --> 28:38.006
But how can a reindeer fly?

28:38.550 --> 28:41.468
Oh, that's easy. It's those antlers. They...

28:41.511 --> 28:43.804
Well, you know, with the wind and all...

28:43.888 --> 28:46.140
That there creates lift, and...

28:47.934 --> 28:50.811
Hot, hot, hot, hot! Hot, hot!

28:51.229 --> 28:54.773
Still, it's a lot of work for one guy.

28:55.316 --> 28:57.151
And that's why
we leave him these cookies

28:57.277 --> 28:59.278
for a quick pick-me-up, up... Whoa!

29:00.655 --> 29:03.907
But it just doesn't
quite make sense, Dad.

29:04.951 --> 29:06.827
Mmm, chestnuts.

29:09.914 --> 29:11.665
(GOOFY HUMMING)

29:12.041 --> 29:13.834
Where are we going, Dad?

29:13.918 --> 29:16.086
Going to share
the joy of Christmas with those

29:16.171 --> 29:17.671
a little less fortunate.

29:17.797 --> 29:20.215
Well, shouldn't Santa be doing this?

29:20.508 --> 29:24.052
Oh, Santy's on a very tight schedule
this time of year,

29:24.179 --> 29:26.263
so we're giving him a helping hand.

29:26.389 --> 29:28.348
Whoa!

29:29.434 --> 29:32.060
(CHUCKLES)
Looks like l might need one, too.

29:38.693 --> 29:40.652
(LAUGHING)

29:42.197 --> 29:44.114
(IMITATING CAR ENGINES)

29:47.202 --> 29:48.285
Hey.

29:49.037 --> 29:50.579
Wanna play toy "carses"?

29:50.663 --> 29:53.707
I only gots two, but you can have one.

29:54.584 --> 29:57.085
Santa gave me this one last year.

29:57.629 --> 30:00.130
This year I hope
he's gonna give me another one.

30:02.050 --> 30:05.552
You know, kid,
I ain't so sure there is such a thing as...

30:05.678 --> 30:08.180
Christmas Eve dinner is served!

30:09.432 --> 30:11.725
Whoa!

30:14.813 --> 30:15.979
(GRUNTS)

30:19.025 --> 30:20.025
(LAUGHING)

30:20.276 --> 30:21.443
Oh!

30:23.404 --> 30:25.072
-MAN: (CHUCKLES) Oh, my!
-CHILDREN: Wow!

30:25.406 --> 30:28.242
-Mr. Goofy, that's incredible!
-That was like magic!

30:28.284 --> 30:30.536
Gosh! (CHUCKLES)

30:31.246 --> 30:32.871
Christmas magic.

30:39.003 --> 30:43.048
-Thank you so much.
-With things being so tight this year,

30:43.091 --> 30:45.551
well, without you, we wouldn't have...

30:45.593 --> 30:47.678
Aw, don't mention it. (CHUCKLES)

30:47.762 --> 30:49.304
You'd do the same for me.

30:49.597 --> 30:53.725
But have you ever really
actually seen Santa?

30:54.143 --> 30:55.978
He's got a big white beard.

30:56.229 --> 30:58.939
But have you ever
actually seen him in person?

31:00.775 --> 31:02.568
-Where?
-(RUSTLING)

31:04.779 --> 31:06.738
Ho, ho, ho!

31:06.781 --> 31:09.116
-Merry Christmas!
-Santa!

31:09.450 --> 31:10.450
(GASPS) Santa?

31:10.743 --> 31:11.785
-Santa!
-You made it!

31:11.995 --> 31:13.036
MAX: Did you get my letter?

31:13.705 --> 31:15.080
It's Santa!

31:15.123 --> 31:18.125
Who wants to be the first
to sit on Santy's lap?

31:18.209 --> 31:20.878
-Me, me, me! Here!
-Santa, me!

31:21.004 --> 31:22.963
Santa, me! Pick me!

31:23.423 --> 31:26.592
I'm so glad you came! Wow!

31:26.634 --> 31:28.510
I almost didn't believe anymore.

31:28.595 --> 31:29.845
But now...

31:30.305 --> 31:31.722
Phew.

31:31.806 --> 31:34.516
Everything's okay.

31:35.476 --> 31:39.062
So, I want my very own
one-of-a-kind, carbon-fiber,

31:39.147 --> 31:44.151
torque-rod, snappy-flex, tip-to-tail,
rail-to-rail, twin-directional snowboard.

31:44.402 --> 31:46.236
Uh, please.

31:46.321 --> 31:47.321
(LAUGHING)

31:49.866 --> 31:50.866
Dad?

31:50.950 --> 31:51.950
Oh...

31:52.160 --> 31:55.537
You tricked me! How could you?

31:56.247 --> 31:58.332
Uh... Ho, ho...

31:58.374 --> 32:00.751
Santy's got a little problem
with one of his elves,

32:00.835 --> 32:02.794
but he'll be right back...

32:13.765 --> 32:17.017
Gosh, Maxie, I'm real sorry.

32:18.561 --> 32:20.938
I was just trying
to make those kids happy.

32:22.565 --> 32:24.358
Remember the old Goof tradition

32:24.400 --> 32:27.110
of eating one of Santy's cookies
before bedtime?

32:27.654 --> 32:28.862
What's the point?

32:30.198 --> 32:33.325
And remember
how we always open just one present

32:33.451 --> 32:34.868
on Christmas Eve?

32:43.461 --> 32:45.379
(HIGH-PITCHED) Hiya, Maxie!

32:45.546 --> 32:48.548
(NORMAL VOICE) Why, looky here.
It's your ol' stuffed bear.

32:48.675 --> 32:51.677
-Remember what you named him?
-Old Stuffed Bear.

32:52.804 --> 32:54.638
Remember who gave him to you?

32:54.931 --> 32:57.182
Yeah. Santa.

32:57.433 --> 32:59.267
But that's when I was little.

32:59.560 --> 33:02.771
(SINGING) Oh, you better watch out
You better not cry

33:02.855 --> 33:05.565
You better not pout
I'm a-telling you why

33:05.650 --> 33:09.403
Santy Claus is coming to town

33:09.529 --> 33:12.489
-No, he's not!
-(HIGH-PITCHED) Trust me, Max.

33:12.573 --> 33:16.034
You just gotta believe. Santy's real.

33:16.077 --> 33:18.829
-No, he's not!
-(NORMAL VOICE) Yes, he is!

33:18.913 --> 33:20.747
No, he's not!

33:20.832 --> 33:21.873
(CLATTERING)

33:28.548 --> 33:29.756
I promise.

33:31.175 --> 33:32.718
Then prove it!

33:34.137 --> 33:37.639
When Santy shows up,
we'll be right here to greet him.

33:37.724 --> 33:39.808
And then I'll snap a picture of him

33:39.892 --> 33:42.894
so you'll always have
the photographic evidence.

33:43.021 --> 33:46.440
(SCOFFS) Yeah.
If you don't fall off the roof first.

33:46.774 --> 33:49.484
Oh, I won't fall off the roof, Maxie.

33:49.736 --> 33:51.111
You just watch.

33:51.154 --> 33:52.362
(SLEIGH BELLS RINGING)

33:52.947 --> 33:55.532
Santy Claus is coming to town!

33:56.325 --> 33:57.659
Oh!

33:58.786 --> 33:59.828
Bright!

34:00.288 --> 34:01.580
(DOG BARKING)

34:05.460 --> 34:06.877
Whoa!

34:08.545 --> 34:09.545
Ooh!

34:11.466 --> 34:13.632
Told you you'd fall off the roof.

34:13.676 --> 34:16.178
I didn't fall off the roof. Whoa!

34:17.346 --> 34:20.181
Where's Santy? I didn't miss him, did I?

34:20.266 --> 34:23.101
-Nope.
-Then where is he?

34:27.690 --> 34:31.318
I don't know about you,
but I'm cold and tired.

34:31.360 --> 34:33.737
And Santa Claus is not coming.

34:52.547 --> 34:54.299
(SNIFFLING)

34:54.425 --> 34:55.675
(SNEEZES)

35:14.946 --> 35:16.113
(CREAKING)

35:28.209 --> 35:32.003
Why doesn't he just grow up
and face the facts?

35:41.180 --> 35:43.265
"Don't forget

35:44.517 --> 35:45.892
"Max."

35:46.018 --> 35:47.561
Aw, Dad.

35:51.482 --> 35:53.859
GOOFY: Max! Wake up! Look, son!

35:54.026 --> 35:56.695
Look! It's him! It really is!

35:57.363 --> 36:00.574
Do you see him, Maxie?
Do you? Huh? Huh? Do you?

36:00.616 --> 36:04.411
Yoo-hoo! Santy! Over here!

36:05.371 --> 36:07.080
Oh, I almost forgot.

36:07.165 --> 36:08.874
Smile, Santy!

36:09.000 --> 36:11.293
-Dad, the lens cap!
-Oops!

36:11.752 --> 36:14.004
I'll get it right this time for sure.

36:15.923 --> 36:17.841
(POLICE SIRENS WAILING)

36:19.594 --> 36:21.928
Come down from the roof
with your hands up.

36:21.971 --> 36:23.763
We have you surrounded.

36:26.142 --> 36:29.603
What in the name of Pete
is going on here, for Pete's sake?

36:29.937 --> 36:32.314
Maybe he's running a little late?

36:38.988 --> 36:40.530
Whoa!

36:40.615 --> 36:42.282
Dad! Dad!

36:44.452 --> 36:45.827
Are you okay?

36:46.621 --> 36:48.622
You were right about everything.

36:49.373 --> 36:51.416
I even fell off the roof.

36:57.340 --> 36:59.507
Hey, Dad, it's okay.

36:59.592 --> 37:02.052
So Santa didn't show. No biggie.

37:04.180 --> 37:08.975
Well, since he's not coming,
at least we can eat all his cookies.

37:09.727 --> 37:10.810
I'm not hungry.

37:13.564 --> 37:14.773
Hey, Dad.

37:14.815 --> 37:17.067
Here's something from me!
Open her up.

37:18.152 --> 37:19.486
Maybe later.

37:23.491 --> 37:26.493
(SINGING) Oh, you better watch out
You better not cry

37:26.535 --> 37:28.703
You better not pout I'm telling you why

37:28.829 --> 37:32.999
'Cause Santa Claus is coming to town

37:45.846 --> 37:47.389
(SIGHS)

37:48.557 --> 37:49.599
(CLATTERING)

37:49.684 --> 37:50.767
Max?

37:52.186 --> 37:53.812
(GASPS) Burglars!

37:54.355 --> 37:55.897
Whoa!

37:57.525 --> 37:58.566
(GASPS)

37:58.651 --> 38:00.610
(STUTTERING) Santy!

38:00.736 --> 38:02.821
Ho, ho, (CLEARS THROAT) ho.

38:03.197 --> 38:05.740
Merry Christmas!

38:05.825 --> 38:09.035
Santy! I'm so happy you came!

38:09.912 --> 38:12.664
Gosh. I thought you'd be taller.

38:14.041 --> 38:16.835
And you look trimmer
than you do in your pictures.

38:17.044 --> 38:21.673
Oh, well, you know,
a camera adds 50 pounds.

38:23.301 --> 38:25.051
You have to meet my boy Maxie!

38:25.094 --> 38:29.347
Oh, yeah. I'd love to,
but I gotta get going.

38:29.724 --> 38:32.642
TWo billion kids, 823 a second.

38:33.269 --> 38:35.437
Very tight schedule.

38:35.521 --> 38:38.315
Wait, Santy!
He's around here somewheres.

38:39.483 --> 38:41.359
Wait! Santy!

38:42.028 --> 38:43.194
Santy!

38:44.822 --> 38:45.905
(GASPS)

38:47.325 --> 38:50.076
-Maxie?
-Hi, Dad.

38:51.412 --> 38:54.998
What are you doing
dressed up like Santy Claus?

38:55.458 --> 38:59.294
I just wanted to make you happy,
like you did for our neighbors.

38:59.920 --> 39:03.131
Oh, Maxie, I might have let you down,

39:03.549 --> 39:05.925
but you sure didn't let me down.

39:08.095 --> 39:09.679
(SLEIGH BELLS RINGING)

39:14.226 --> 39:17.103
Could it be? Do you think?

39:17.605 --> 39:20.607
Gosh, it sure looks like

39:21.192 --> 39:23.610
-Santa Claus!
-Santa Claus?

39:24.028 --> 39:26.029
I believe it is.

39:29.533 --> 39:34.454
Wow. My very own, one-of-a-kind,
carbon-fiber, torque-rod, snappy-flex,

39:34.538 --> 39:37.582
tip-to-tail, rail-to-rail,
wood core, torsionally stiff,

39:37.625 --> 39:39.834
twin-directional snowboard!

39:39.919 --> 39:41.252
(SNIFFS)

39:41.295 --> 39:42.587
Thanks, Santa.

39:42.963 --> 39:45.131
What's all the commotion out here?

39:45.257 --> 39:48.718
If it's another robber,
I'm gonna get him...

39:50.304 --> 39:52.180
Ooh! Santa?

39:52.515 --> 39:55.558
Well, hey! Hey, Santa!

39:55.643 --> 39:57.852
I believed in you all along!

39:58.020 --> 40:01.189
For real and for true!
So where are my presents?

40:06.821 --> 40:10.782
SANTA CLAUS: Ho, ho, ho!
Merry Christmas!

40:12.076 --> 40:15.662
But what about my squirty gun
and my yo-yo?

40:16.831 --> 40:18.706
I know you can hear me!

40:19.041 --> 40:21.626
Santa didn't forget your gift, did he?

40:22.128 --> 40:26.673
Every year I ask or the same gift,
and every year, I get it.

40:27.007 --> 40:29.676
-What's that?
-Your happiness.

40:29.760 --> 40:31.010
Uh-oh.

40:31.053 --> 40:32.303
What is it, son?

40:32.346 --> 40:35.348
(CHUCKLES) Got you the same thing.

40:36.016 --> 40:37.934
Merry Christmas, Dad.

40:38.018 --> 40:39.894
Merry Christmas, Max.

40:40.354 --> 40:41.855
Where are you going?

40:42.189 --> 40:45.150
l'm gonna go share my new present
with little Jimmy next door.

40:46.277 --> 40:47.902
That's my boy.

40:50.948 --> 40:52.323
(LAUGHING)

40:53.200 --> 40:56.494
NARRATOR: So, Christmas is found
in the way that we live.

40:56.537 --> 40:59.539
Not what we receive,
but what we can give.

41:01.208 --> 41:04.252
Now the last present here
may seem rather small,

41:04.336 --> 41:07.714
not fancy or flashy, or special at all.

41:07.798 --> 41:11.968
But this gift can be given
by the rich or the poor.

41:12.052 --> 41:15.763
It's a gift of the heart,
and it means so much more.

41:28.569 --> 41:30.987
Thanks, Joe! Merry Christmas!

41:31.405 --> 41:34.240
Merry Christmas, George.
You working tonight?

41:34.450 --> 41:36.993
Not tonight! It's Christmas Eve!

41:43.375 --> 41:45.084
(PLAYING)

41:59.308 --> 42:01.100
(BARKING)

42:04.855 --> 42:06.606
There it is, Pluto,

42:06.690 --> 42:09.567
the perfect gift
to go with Minnie's watch.

42:10.778 --> 42:12.612
(SIGHS) My Minnie.

42:15.241 --> 42:16.699
They close at 5:00?

42:16.784 --> 42:18.451
Well, I'm a little short right now,

42:18.494 --> 42:21.746
but you and I are gonna make
lots of tips today.

42:21.830 --> 42:23.998
-Aren't we, fella?
-Yeah! Yeah! Yeah! (PANTING)

42:24.625 --> 42:26.626
We'll stop by right after work
and pick it up.

42:26.669 --> 42:29.295
Come on. Let's get this tree
over to Minnie's.

42:29.338 --> 42:30.463
(BARKING)

42:34.426 --> 42:37.595
MINNIE: Oh, Figaro,
there's nothing but bills!

42:37.805 --> 42:38.846
(MEOWS)

42:39.306 --> 42:42.100
How am I ever going to afford
to get Mickey a present?

42:42.142 --> 42:43.142
(DOOR OPENS)

42:49.942 --> 42:51.067
(PURRING)

42:55.406 --> 42:57.574
Aw, Mickey! (GIGGLES)

42:57.658 --> 43:01.244
When you play your harmonica,
my heart sings!

43:02.454 --> 43:06.332
You know, an instrument like that
deserves a special case.

43:07.960 --> 43:10.086
Oh, yeah. Someday.

43:10.170 --> 43:11.879
(SINGING) La la-la-la la la

43:11.964 --> 43:14.674
Come on into the kitchen.
Breakfast is almost ready.

43:17.928 --> 43:18.928
(SHRIEKS)

43:21.515 --> 43:23.641
You sure I'm not eating you
out of house and home?

43:23.684 --> 43:26.227
'Course not, silly. I have plenty.

43:28.647 --> 43:29.647
Ta-da!

43:29.982 --> 43:31.065
Aw, for me?

43:31.150 --> 43:32.525
Uh-huh! (GIGGLES)

43:33.527 --> 43:36.195
You wouldn't happen
to have the time, would you, Minnie?

43:36.322 --> 43:38.906
-Well, let's see. It's...
-Gosh.

43:38.991 --> 43:40.700
Sure is a beautiful watch!

43:40.826 --> 43:43.202
MINNIE: (SIGHS) My one heirloom.

43:43.704 --> 43:45.413
I'll bet it'd look real nice

43:45.497 --> 43:47.665
with a gold chain
around your pretty neck.

43:47.791 --> 43:49.751
-MINNIE: Aw, Mickey.
-(MICKEY CHUCKLES)

43:49.835 --> 43:52.295
Oh, my goodness! I've gotta go to work!

43:54.256 --> 43:57.133
Madam, your sleigh awaits!

44:00.095 --> 44:02.055
Oh, how wonderful.

44:03.223 --> 44:04.932
(IMITATES HORSE)

44:05.893 --> 44:07.518
Giddyap, Pluto!

44:21.909 --> 44:23.117
(GIGGLES)

44:24.870 --> 44:26.579
See you tonight!

44:27.081 --> 44:29.749
-Come on, fella. We got work to do!
-(BARKING)

44:30.668 --> 44:32.085
(MUSIC PLAYING)

44:32.127 --> 44:35.254
PETE: (RECORDED)
Welcome to Crazy Pete's Tree Lot!

44:35.297 --> 44:38.341
Hurry, folks.
Only one more day till Christmas!

44:38.467 --> 44:41.386
Easy credit, no money down!
(LAUGHS)

44:48.977 --> 44:52.605
Hey! This stuff works pretty good!
(CHUCKLING)

44:52.648 --> 44:54.440
Merry Christmas, Mr. Crazy Pete.

44:54.525 --> 44:58.945
Aw, merry-shmerry. I'll be merry
when I've sold all those 10-footers!

45:00.656 --> 45:03.783
Why are you standing there
with your face hanging out?

45:03.992 --> 45:05.535
Get to work!

45:08.122 --> 45:10.331
Okay, fella. You know what to do.

45:10.416 --> 45:11.708
Shake a leg!

45:31.061 --> 45:33.312
PETE: Quit slacking over there!
There's a customer waiting!

45:36.775 --> 45:39.777
Oh, do be careful of the paint.

45:40.154 --> 45:43.531
-Yes, ma'am!
-Such a nice young man.

45:44.199 --> 45:46.492
Here's a little something for you.

45:46.660 --> 45:50.079
Gosh, I don't expect anything.
I'm just glad to help.

45:51.457 --> 45:54.000
Oh, boy! Thank you, ma'am.

45:54.251 --> 45:55.668
Thank you!

45:56.712 --> 46:00.923
Hot dog! Looks like I'll finally be able
to get Minnie that chain for her watch.

46:01.008 --> 46:02.300
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah!

46:02.342 --> 46:04.010
Uh, we'd like to buy a tree...

46:04.094 --> 46:06.679
Did I hear you folks
are looking for a tree?

46:06.764 --> 46:10.516
Boy, oh, boy! Is this your lucky day!
(CHUCKLES)

46:11.560 --> 46:16.981
This here's what you folks need.
Ten feet of towering Nova Scotia pine.

46:17.858 --> 46:22.236
Wow. It's bigger than our house.

46:22.905 --> 46:25.406
Well, it's a little more than we need.

46:25.574 --> 46:28.242
Well, missus,
I gotta be honest with you.

46:28.410 --> 46:31.662
This is all I got left on the lot!

46:31.705 --> 46:34.290
The others have been
"reservated" in advance.

46:35.292 --> 46:39.796
You don't want these kids
going without a tree, now, do you?

46:39.880 --> 46:40.880
(COUGHING)

46:40.964 --> 46:43.382
We are gonna get a tree,
aren't we, Daddy?

46:43.425 --> 46:45.927
Um, this is all we have.

46:46.011 --> 46:50.056
Well, that'll be just fine
(CHUCKLES) for a down payment.

46:50.265 --> 46:52.725
I'll set you up
with a nice installment plan.

46:52.851 --> 46:55.520
All's you gotta do is sign here!

46:55.771 --> 46:57.772
(SINGSONG) We're gonna get a tree

46:57.856 --> 46:59.649
We're gonna get a tree

47:00.067 --> 47:02.568
Get your foot off the brake, Pops.
The kids are waiting.

47:02.736 --> 47:04.529
MICKEY: Hey! How about this tree?

47:05.364 --> 47:07.573
I found it out back.

47:08.242 --> 47:10.743
It hasn't been "reservated." (GULPS)

47:12.746 --> 47:14.455
Wow!

47:14.540 --> 47:16.082
It's beautiful.

47:16.124 --> 47:17.250
It's perfect!

47:17.334 --> 47:18.709
We'll take it.

47:19.294 --> 47:20.962
(GROWLS)

47:21.338 --> 47:23.840
MAN: Merry Christmas!
And thank you again.

47:24.049 --> 47:25.925
-Thanks a lot!
-Merry Christmas!

47:26.093 --> 47:28.344
-(GROWLING)
-So long! Merry...

47:29.972 --> 47:31.222
Christmas.

47:31.598 --> 47:34.100
I had them on the hook
for a 10-foot tree!

47:34.476 --> 47:35.518
(CHUCKLES MEEKLY)

47:35.602 --> 47:39.939
I'm taking what I would have made
off of that tree out of your pay!

47:40.107 --> 47:41.607
(GROWLING)

47:42.109 --> 47:43.276
But I...

47:43.318 --> 47:44.527
(BARKING)

47:44.611 --> 47:46.279
-Whoa!
-Now get off of my lot!

47:46.697 --> 47:47.905
(BOTH GRUNTING)

47:48.699 --> 47:50.366
(SCOFFS) Chumps.

47:53.287 --> 47:54.579
(SNIFFING)

47:54.621 --> 47:56.956
Hmm, somebody's burning their ham.

47:59.459 --> 48:00.459
(YELLING)

48:02.421 --> 48:04.297
